               <p>JOHN BASTAR. I am a <rs id="t18280911-225-viclabel1150" type="occupation">mechanic</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280911-225-victim1286 t18280911-225-viclabel1150"></join>; the prisoners were in my employ: I sent Perkins and Berry on an errand to Thames-street, to purchase some sheets of copper; I gave Berry two sovereigns, out of which he was to pay for the copper; he brought me this bill, but neither of the prisoners were there at the time - I never heard from either of the prisoners what sum of money was paid.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280911-225-person1287">
                  WALTER 
                  BERRY
               <interp inst="t18280911-225-person1287" type="surname" value="BERRY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-225-person1287" type="given" value="WALTER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-225-person1287" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was in the employ of Mr. Bastar. I went with Perkins to buy this copper; we paid 1l. 11s. 10d. for it - I gave my master the bill.</p>
               <p>COURT to JOHN BASTAR. Q. What was the sum you was told they paid? A. 1l. 19s. 4d., agreeable to this bill- I gave them the two sovereigns to pay for the copper, and accuse them of stealing the difference.</p>
